sfpsSapTable.name: sfpsSapTable
sfpsSapTable.description: This table contains the registered (active) call processors indexed (indirectly) by address and address type supported.

sfpsSapTableEntry.name: sfpsSapTableEntry
sfpsSapTableEntry.description: Each entry contains information pertaining to an active call processor.

sfpsSapTableTag.name: sfpsSapTableTag
sfpsSapTableTag.description: A type tag used to sort and index the table entries.

sfpsSapTableHash.name: sfpsSapTableHash
sfpsSapTableHash.description: A hash of the sfpsSapTableAddress used to identify the instance.

sfpsSapTableHashIndex.name: sfpsSapTableHashIndex
sfpsSapTableHashIndex.description: A count of the non-unique sfpsSapTableAddress hashes used to identify the instance.

sfpsSapTableSourceCP.name: sfpsSapTableSourceCP
sfpsSapTableSourceCP.description: The name of the call processor initiating the the SAP attempts for this particular SAP load.

sfpsSapTableDestCP.name: sfpsSapTableDestCP
sfpsSapTableDestCP.description: The destination call processor that is registered for with this source call processor for the given SAP load.

sfpsSapTableSAP.name: sfpsSapTableSAP
sfpsSapTableSAP.description: The value of the SAP in 0x format.

sfpsSapTableOperStatus.name: sfpsSapTableOperStatus
sfpsSapTableOperStatus.description: Displays the Current OperStatus of the SAP entry.

sfpsSapTableAdminStatus.name: sfpsSapTableAdminStatus
sfpsSapTableAdminStatus.description: Displays the Current AdminStatus of the SAP entry.

sfpsSapTableStateTime.name: sfpsSapTableStateTime
sfpsSapTableStateTime.description: Total number of SFPSElements stored in NVRAM for persistence.

sfpsSapAPIVerb.name: sfpsSapAPIVerb
sfpsSapAPIVerb.description: 1 - getStatus -- The default verb. When the SourceCP, DestCP, and SAP info are entered, this action will get the current AdminStatus, OperStatus, and NvramStatus. (Must perform a mo_get after setting the above info to actually get the status info) 2 - next -- Move to the next Entry in the SAP Table and Get the status. If this operation is successful, the verb will stay next, else it defaults to getStatus. 3 - first -- Jump back to the First Entry in the SAP Table. 4 - disable -- Disable the Current SAP Entry. This does not effect the Status of this Entry in Nvram. 5 - disableInNvram -- Set the Current SAP Entries status to Disabled in Nvram - This does not effect the Current Admin Status for this SAP Entry. 6 - enable -- Enable the Current SAP Entry. This does not effect the Status of this Entry in Nvram. 7 - enableInNvram -- Set the Current SAP Entries status to Enabled in Nvram - This does not effect the Current Admin Status for this SAP Entry. 8 - clearFromNvram -- Clear the Current SAP Entry from Nvram (if set). 9 - clearAllNvram -- Clear all SAP Entries from Nvram. 10 - resetStats -- Resets the Accepted/Dropped Stats for the Current/Entered SAP Entry. 11 - resetAllStats -- Resets the Accepted/Dropped Stats for all SAP Entries.

sfpsSapAPISourceCP.name: sfpsSapAPISourceCP
sfpsSapAPISourceCP.description: The name of the call processor initiating the the SAP attempts for this particular SAP load.

sfpsSapAPIDestCP.name: sfpsSapAPIDestCP
sfpsSapAPIDestCP.description: The destination call processor that is registered for with this source call processor for the given SAP load.

sfpsSapAPISAP.name: sfpsSapAPISAP
sfpsSapAPISAP.description: Enter in the SAP for the desired SAP Entry.

sfpsSapAPINVStatus.name: sfpsSapAPINVStatus
sfpsSapAPINVStatus.description: Displays the Current Admin Status of this SAP Entry saved in Nvram.

sfpsSapAPIAdminStatus.name: sfpsSapAPIAdminStatus
sfpsSapAPIAdminStatus.description: Displays the Current AdminStatus of the SAP Entry.

sfpsSapAPIOperStatus.name: sfpsSapAPIOperStatus
sfpsSapAPIOperStatus.description: Displays the Current OperStatus of the SAP Entry.

sfpsSapAPINvSet.name: sfpsSapAPINvSet
sfpsSapAPINvSet.description: Total number of entries stored in NVRAM for persistence.

sfpsSapAPINVTotal.name: sfpsSapAPINVTotal
sfpsSapAPINVTotal.description: Total number of entries allocated in NVRAM. The switch will always allocate enough space in NVRAM for the number of elements. That is, NvTotal will always be greater than or equal to NvSet.

sfpsCallByTupleTable.name: sfpsCallByTupleTable
sfpsCallByTupleTable.description: This table contains the call tags, and call states indexed (indirectly) by switch tuple (in port, src address, dst address)

sfpsCallByTupleEntry.name: sfpsCallByTupleEntry
sfpsCallByTupleEntry.description: Each entry contains information pertaining to a call tag and its state.

sfpsCallByTupleInPort.name: sfpsCallByTupleInPort
sfpsCallByTupleInPort.description: Port of the switch on which the packet associated with this call tag was seen.

sfpsCallByTupleSrcHash.name: sfpsCallByTupleSrcHash

sfpsCallByTupleDstHash.name: sfpsCallByTupleDstHash
sfpsCallByTupleDstHash.description: A hash of sfpsCallByTupleTopDstAddress used to identify the instance.

sfpsCallByTupleHashIndex.name: sfpsCallByTupleHashIndex
sfpsCallByTupleHashIndex.description: A count of non-unique sfpsCallByTupleSrcHash and sfpsCallByTupleDstHash pairs used to identify the instance.

sfpsCallByTupleBotSrcType.name: sfpsCallByTupleBotSrcType
sfpsCallByTupleBotSrcType.description: The source address type of the lowest known protocol layer.

sfpsCallByTupleBotSrcAddress.name: sfpsCallByTupleBotSrcAddress
sfpsCallByTupleBotSrcAddress.description: The source address value of the lowest known protocol layer.

sfpsCallByTupleBotDstType.name: sfpsCallByTupleBotDstType
sfpsCallByTupleBotDstType.description: The destination address type of the lowest known protocol layer.

sfpsCallByTupleBotDstAddress.name: sfpsCallByTupleBotDstAddress
sfpsCallByTupleBotDstAddress.description: The destination address value of the lowest known protocol layer.

sfpsCallByTupleTopSrcType.name: sfpsCallByTupleTopSrcType
sfpsCallByTupleTopSrcType.description: The source address type of the highest learned protocol layer.

sfpsCallByTupleTopSrcAddress.name: sfpsCallByTupleTopSrcAddress
sfpsCallByTupleTopSrcAddress.description: The source address value of the highest learned protocol layer.

sfpsCallByTupleTopDstType.name: sfpsCallByTupleTopDstType
sfpsCallByTupleTopDstType.description: The destination address type of the highest learned protocol layer.

sfpsCallByTupleTopDstAddress.name: sfpsCallByTupleTopDstAddress
sfpsCallByTupleTopDstAddress.description: The destination address value of the highest learned protocol layer.

sfpsCallByTupleCallTag.name: sfpsCallByTupleCallTag
sfpsCallByTupleCallTag.description: The number used to reference this packet and its associated calls.

sfpsCallByTupleCallState.name: sfpsCallByTupleCallState
sfpsCallByTupleCallState.description: The current state of the packet in the call processor.

sfpsCallByTupleTimeRemaining.name: sfpsCallByTupleTimeRemaining
sfpsCallByTupleTimeRemaining.description: The number of time ticks remaining before this entry's timer expires and it is removed from the table.

sfpsCallTableStatsRam.name: sfpsCallTableStatsRam
sfpsCallTableStatsRam.description: The number of bytes used by the Call Table.

sfpsCallTableStatsSize.name: sfpsCallTableStatsSize
sfpsCallTableStatsSize.description: The number of entries in the Call Table.

sfpsCallTableStatsInUse.name: sfpsCallTableStatsInUse
sfpsCallTableStatsInUse.description: The current number of calls in use. A call goes into this table only if it is being blocked (waiting for resolve or sent new user).

sfpsCallTableStatsMax.name: sfpsCallTableStatsMax
sfpsCallTableStatsMax.description: The maximum number of calls that the switch maintained.

sfpsCallTableStatsTotMisses.name: sfpsCallTableStatsTotMisses
sfpsCallTableStatsTotMisses.description: The number of times that there were no calls available in the Call Table. This would be the number of calls that had to be dropped.

sfpsCallTableStatsLastMiss.name: sfpsCallTableStatsLastMiss
sfpsCallTableStatsLastMiss.description: Number of calls dropped in last miss, also write 0 to files
